Hey everyone!

I don't really know which channel to post this question to.

We work with a hotel reservation tool (<https://www.hoteliers.com>). We have a page over there where people can book their hotel room. We are currently building our website in the HubSpot CMS and we want to implement a small form that makes a POST request to the reservation tool. If we use plain html and create a form, it works! But the input fields are not styled. We can put inline css there, that's not the problem.

But we'll like it if we can add a datepicker to these fields. Is there an ID or class we can set to get the HubSpot cms native datepicker (to match it with other froms we made within the CMS)?

Or is there another way to achieve this with the native form builder tool?

Example of working form in plain html:

```&lt;form class="hoteliers-book-form" method="post" target="_blank" action="<http://www.hoteliers.com/wlpEngine.php?ID=2990&amp;lang=nl>"&gt;
    &lt;input name="arrival" type="text" value="2020-11-01"&gt;
    &lt;input name="departure" type="text" value="2020-11-10"&gt;
    &lt;button type="submit"&gt;Beschikbaarheid&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/form&gt;```
Thanks in advance!
